**Category:** essay-draft faith truth aquinas lindbeck practical-knowledge marshall

**Abstract:**
Substantial essay titled "The question of truth concerning faith" engaging Bruce Marshall's "Aquinas as Postliberal Theologian." Argues against Aquinas's conception of faith as an epistemic act of assent aiming at correspondence with reality. Proposes instead that faith is closer to Aristotelian practical knowledge--prudentia as dispositional project realized in theological orthopraxis, not intellectual assent. Includes extended analysis of animal knowledge, dramatic space, and speculative versus practical knowledge.

**AI Recommendation:** Major theoretical essay; central to faith-as-practical-knowledge thesis.

